  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/27009319" />
    <a title="A.C." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/368979-a-c"><img alt="A.C." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1324963202p2/368979.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/27009319?book_show_action=true">Jul 11, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="A.C." class="user" itemprop="url" name="A.C." href="/user/show/368979-a-c">A.C.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">anyone</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer27009319" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8514128373113123231">I picked this book up on a fluke in Jamaica after I finished reading a John Feinstein book. I&apos;m glad that I did because this book is incredible. It&apos;s about the breaking of one man&apos;s soul in post-Nkrumah Ghana. It&apos;s simple, it&apos;s sparse, it&apos;s striking. The decay of the character and the people surrounding him are similar to that of Nausea by Sartre. But, whatever I say, it&apos;s not going to do this book justice. Stop reading this right now. Go get this book and read it from cover to cover in one sitt</span>
  <span id="freeText8514128373113123231" style="display:none">I picked this book up on a fluke in Jamaica after I finished reading a John Feinstein book. I'm glad that I did because this book is incredible. It's about the breaking of one man's soul in post-Nkrumah Ghana. It's simple, it's sparse, it's striking. The decay of the character and the people surrounding him are similar to that of Nausea by Sartre. But, whatever I say, it's not going to do this book justice. Stop reading this right now. Go get this book and read it from cover to cover in one sitting (it's short). This book is so good, I sent it to my friend in Nevada, and I never send people books. Ever. Think about that, and then go get it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8514128373113123231" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


